Residents in San Bernardino County in California were forced to flee their homes after
planned control burn in an area of brush land went out of control due to high winds
The county parks department set the fire on Tuesday to clear the area of highly flammable cattails
Residents were forced to flee their homes as the fire approached their properties near Victorville
San Bernardino County Fire Chief Mark Hartwig told the Los Angeles Times that he anticipated the fire should be fully doused later today
